PR DESCRIPTION:
### Bugs fixed by this PR 

- Resolves #45349
- Resolves #8446 
- Resolves #42000
- Resolves #42006
- Resolves #44320
- Resolves #38987 
- Resolves #46383
- Resolves https://github.com/quarkiverse/quarkus-pact/issues/272

### Bugs created by this PR (doh!)

- Creates #45785 
- Creates #46542

### Outstanding issues/breaking changes (input to release notes)

- `@TestProfile` on `@Nested` tests are not supported anymore (fixes #45349).
- Version 3 of Maven Surefire and Failsafe is required, and version 2 is unlikely to work.
- Changes the order of some tests; tests should not depend on execution order if they don't set one explicitly, so this *shouldn't* cause customer failures, but it did cause failures for us (see, for example, #45955 and #45960)
- Dev services start in the discovery phase (#45785, we know how to fix this quickly)
- Increased memory footprint running tests. For suites using multiple profiles and resources, more metaspace may be needed.
- Accessing ConfigProvider from a custom JUnit condition results in ServiceConfigurationError · Issue #47081 · workaround is to set a TCCL to `this.getClass().getClassLoader()`
- Whatever causes https://github.com/quarkiverse/quarkiverse/issues/55#issuecomment-2812323118, diagnosis TBD

### What problem is this solving? 

We see a lot of problems caused by the fact that we load test classes with the deployment classloader, and then intercept the execution and reload the classes with the runtime class

